# face-recognition-contract
Face Recognition Docker smart-contract for [Vostok platform](https://github.com/vostokplatform/Vostok-Releases/releases).
There was used great [face_recognition](https://github.com/ageitgey/face_recognition) python library using dlib neural network.

# Deploy

Before the usage script should be deployed to the docker registry. For testing, you can start a local docker registry using

```
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name registry registry:2
docker build -t $(basename "$PWD") .
docker image tag $(basename "$PWD") localhost:5000/$(basename "$PWD")
docker push localhost:5000/$(basename "$PWD")
```

You should use a docker repository that is accessible to all members of your network.
Your vostok address also should have the `contract_developer` permission to create the contract.

# Init

When creating a contract, the neural network parameters of the persons that the contract can recognize should be passed.
The initial parameters must begin with the string 'face_' and have used username, and the type must be 'binary', and in the value must be a serialized array using the `sample/serialize_face.py` script.

```
curl -X POST --header 'Content-Type: application/json' --header 'Accept: application/json' --header 'X-API-Key: vostok' -d '{ \ 
 "sender": "3NBaZHxoew31ZZXBpThQ1Kfv6MpVeKapYyA", \ 
 "image": "localhost:5000/face-recognition-contract", \ 
 "imageHash": "efd2a822f063dbc3007785535eac404bfca596b5b3ae10d42b2f5c46187cae8e", \ 
 "params": [{"key":"face_sasha","type":"binary","value":""}], \ 
 "fee": 0, \ 
 "type": 103 \ 
 }' 'http://localhost:6862/contracts/create'
 ```
 
 # Call
 
 To call this contract, the first parameter should be the image encoded using the `sample/serialize_image.py` script with any name with 'binary' type. You can change the parameters of the script to increase the quality of the returned image, but it is worth remembering that the size of the returned image will also increase.
 
```
curl -X POST --header 'Content-Type: application/json' --header 'Accept: application/json' --header 'X-API-Key: vostok' -d '{ \ 
 "sender": "3NBaZHxoew31ZZXBpThQ1Kfv6MpVeKapYyA", \ 
 "contractId": "9NAqQdiGFfkH3gCR9UHwnDSVsuSoSmHJ8SVLDfhTuTcS", \ 
 "params": [{"key":"image","type":"binary","value":""}], \ 
 "fee": 0, \

 }' 'http://localhost:6862/contracts/execute'
 ```
